    "def forward(self, x, entropy=None):\n",
    "    safe_b = torch.abs(self.b) + 1e-4\n",
    "    \n",
    "    if entropy is not None:\n",
    "      dilation_factor = 1.0 - torch.clamp(entropy, 0, 0.99)\n",
    "      safe_b = safe_b * dilation_factor.view(-1, 1, 1, 1)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "1b09c69d",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "The Safety Net: Since b is learnable, gradient descent might try to push it to 0 or into negative numbers.\n",
    "\n",
    " If b becomes negative, the exponential term $e^{-b x^2}$ blows up to infinity, outputting NaN and bricking your model. \n",
    " \n",
    " torch.abs() keeps it positive, and + 1e-4 ensures it never hits absolute zero."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "id": "74ddbcd5",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "return self.a * x * torch.exp(-safe_b * torch.pow(x, 2)) + self.c * x"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "5d67e4a8",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "### The Core Calculus: Here is the  mathematical reality: $f(x) = a \\cdot x \\cdot e^{-k x^2} + c \\cdot x$ Why it exists:\n",
    "\n",
    " When the network is highly confused (High Entropy, so $b \\to 0$), the equation morphs into $a \\cdot x \\cdot 1 + c \\cdot x$. \n",
    " \n",
    " It basically becomes a straight line.\n",
    " \n",
    "  You are opening the floodgates, letting raw, uncompressed gradients flow backward to help the network learn.\n",
    "  \n",
    "   When the network is confident (Low Entropy), $b$ returns to normal, and the function pinches off, acting as a strict, non linear feature selector."
   ]
  },
